==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: keratin
<hw>ker"a*tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ke`ras</grk>, <grk>-atos</grk>, horn.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A sulfur-containing fibrous protein constituting the
main structural protein of hard epidermal tissues, such as horn, hair,
feathers, nails, claws, hoofs, and the like. It is an insoluble
substance, and, unlike elastin, is not dissolved even by gastric or
pancreatic juice. By decomposition with sulphuric acid it yields leucine
and tyrosine plus various other acid-stable amino acids. The amino acid
composition varies, but it usually has a high percentage of cystine,
which stabilizes and insolubilizes the protein by forming intrachain
linkages. A softer form of keratin is present in the epidermis and
whalebone. Called also <altname>epidermose</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Keratitis</ent>⟦br⟧
